---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-06-20';
const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms under which FluxTube is provided as open-source software you self-host."
>
  <main>
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="manhead">
        <span class="manhead-left">terms(7)</span>
        <span class="manhead-center">Conventions</span>
        <span class="manhead-right">{today}</span>
      </div>

      <header class="legal-head">
        <h1>Terms of <em>service.</em></h1>
        <p class="muted updated">
          <span class="updated-label">Last reviewed</span>
          <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>The short answer</h2>
        <p>
          FluxTube is open-source software released under the MIT license. There is no hosted
          service. The "Terms of Service" you're reading exist primarily because the YouTube Data
          API verification process requires that the OAuth client point at a published terms page.
          The substance is: you self-host, you operate it, no warranty.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What FluxTube is</h2>
        <p>
          FluxTube is software for syncing your own unread Miniflux entries into your own YouTube
          playlists. It is distributed as source code at
          <a href="https://github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube">github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          There is no FluxTube SaaS, no shared infrastructure, no central server. Every deployment
          of FluxTube is independent: someone clones the repo, configures it against their own
          accounts, and deploys it to their own Cloudflare account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Self-hosted use</h2>
        <p>By deploying FluxTube to your own infrastructure, you agree that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You are solely responsible for the operation of your instance.</li>
          <li>
            You are solely responsible for compliance with the
            <a href="https://developers.google.com/youtube/terms/api-services-terms-of-service"
              >YouTube API Services Terms of Service</a
            >, the
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google Privacy Policy</a>, and the terms
            of any Miniflux instance you connect to.
          </li>
          <li>
            You will use FluxTube only against YouTube accounts and Miniflux accounts you personally
            control, and not on behalf of others without their explicit consent.
          </li>
          <li>
            You will not use FluxTube to bypass YouTube's quotas, terms, or rate limits in a manner
            that violates Google's Developer Policies.
          </li>
          <li>
            You understand that your YouTube Data API quota is your own; FluxTube does not pool
            quota across users.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Source code license</h2>
        <p>
          FluxTube source code is released under the
          <a href="https://github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT license</a>. That
          license governs the use, modification, and redistribution of the code. The license text
          takes precedence over these Terms for matters of code rights and warranty disclaimers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>No warranty</h2>
        <p>
          FluxTube is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including
          but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
          and noninfringement. The author is not liable for any claim, damages, or other liability
          arising from the use of the software — including but not limited to data loss, API quota
          exhaustion, YouTube account actions, or Miniflux state corruption.
        </p>
        <p>
          This mirrors the MIT license. In plainer language: if FluxTube does the wrong thing with
          your playlists or marks the wrong entries read, you wear the consequences. Audit the code
          before you give it write access to your accounts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>The marketing page</h2>
        <p>
          This page (<code>fluxtube.forklabs.cc</code>) is a static site published for
          discoverability and to satisfy the Google OAuth verification requirements (a terms page
          and privacy policy at a verified domain). Using this page does not create a service
          relationship between you and the author.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          The "Last updated" date at the top of this page changes when the terms change. The full
          revision history is available via Git on the
          <a href="https://github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube">FluxTube source repository</a> for this page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:alghanmi@gmail.com">alghanmi@gmail.com</a>.
          Source and issue tracker:
          <a href="https://github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube">github.com/alghanmi/fluxtube</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="see-also-h" class="see-also">
        <h2 id="see-also-h" class="manh2">See also</h2>
        <ul class="see-list" role="list">
          <li>
            <a href="/">/</a>
            <span class="see-note subtle">fluxtube landing</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/privacy">/privacy</a>
            <span class="see-note subtle">privacy policy</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://forklabs.cc">forklabs.cc</a>
            <span class="see-note subtle">the umbrella project</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="manhead manhead-foot">
        <span class="manhead-left">terms(7)</span>
        <span class="manhead-center">Conventions</span>
        <span class="manhead-right">{today}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-head {
    padding-block: var(--space-16) var(--space-12);
  }

  .legal-head h1 {
    max-width: 14ch;
  }

  .updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--color-fg-subtle);
    margin-block-start: var(--space-6);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .updated-label {
    margin-inline-end: 0.6ch;
  }

  section h2:not(.manh2) {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--size-xl);
    font-weight: 450;
    font-variation-settings:
      'SOFT' 100,
      'WONK' 0,
      'opsz' 36;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-block: var(--space-10) var(--space-4);
  }

  section p {
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    margin-block: var(--space-3);
  }

  section ul {
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    list-style: none;
    padding-inline-start: var(--space-6);
  }

  section ul li {
    margin-block: var(--space-2);
    position: relative;
  }

  section ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    inset-inline-start: -1.2em;
    color: var(--color-fg-subtle);
  }

  .see-also {
    padding-block-end: var(--space-8);
  }

  .see-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2) var(--space-6);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
  }

  .see-list li {
    display: contents;
  }

  .see-list li::before {
    display: none;
  }

  .see-list li > a {
    color: var(--color-fg);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-line-strong);
    text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
  }

  .see-list li > a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .see-note {
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    align-self: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .see-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-3);
    }
    .see-list li {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-1);
    }
  }
</style>
